STEP 3 — Build Backend (Python Flask)
          backend/app.py
                  from flask import Flask, request
                  import mysql.connector
                  
                  app = Flask(__name__)
                  
                  db = mysql.connector.connect(
                      host="mysql-service",
                      user="root",
                      password="password",
                      database="testdb"
                  )
                  
                  @app.route('/login', methods=['POST'])
                  def login():
                      username = request.form['username']
                      password = request.form['password']
                  
                      cursor = db.cursor()
                      query = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username=%s AND password=%s"
                      cursor.execute(query, (username, password))
                      result = cursor.fetchall()
                  
                      if result:
                          return "Login Successful ✅"
                      else:
                          return "Invalid Credentials ❌"
                  
                  app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=3000)
backend/requirements.txt
                    flask
                    mysql-connector-python
backend/Dockerfile
                  FROM python:3.9
                  WORKDIR /app
                  COPY requirements.txt .
                  RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
                  COPY . .
                  CMD ["python", "app.py"]
STEP 4 — MySQL (Same)
k8s/mysql-deployment.yaml
        apiVersion: apps/v1
        kind: Deployment
        metadata:
          name: mysql
        spec:
          replicas: 1
          selector:
            matchLabels:
              app: mysql
          template:
            metadata:
              labels:
                app: mysql
            spec:
              containers:
              - name: mysql
                image: mysql:5.7
                env:
                - name: MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD
                  value: password
                - name: MYSQL_DATABASE
                  value: testdb
                ports:
                - containerPort: 3306
k8s/mysql-service.yaml
        apiVersion: v1
        kind: Service
        metadata:
          name: mysql-service
        spec:
          ports:
            - port: 3306
          selector:
            app: mysql
STEP 5 — Backend Deployment
            k8s/backend-deployment.yaml
                apiVersion: apps/v1
                kind: Deployment
                metadata:
                  name: backend
                spec:
                  replicas: 1
                  selector:
                    matchLabels:
                      app: backend
                  template:
                    metadata:
                      labels:
                        app: backend
                    spec:
                      containers:
                      - name: backend
                        image: <your-dockerhub-username>/backend:latest
